- Variant used: [e.g. 500-record file, corruption level X — which of the 12 files]
- Train/test split: [e.g. 70/30], random_state = [seed]
- Blocking keys tested: [2], [4], [2,4]
- Epsilon values: 2, 3, 4

## Key results
- ML models (especially SVM and Random Forest) were more resilient to DP noise and data
  corruption than the threshold baseline.
- Best model: SVM (~0.97 F1). Recommended epsilon 3–4 and Counting Bloom Filter encoding.

